hr.fer.zemris.webapps.webapp2.voting

Class BandInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • hr.fer.zemris.webapps.webapp2.voting.BandInfo

  • public class BandInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    BandInfo contains information about a single band.
    Static methods for creating BandInfo objects from String and from files are available.
    Author:
    Dan

      • fromString

        public static BandInfo fromString(java.lang.String str)
        Creates a new BandInfo from given String.
        Number of votes for the band is set to 0.
        Parameters:
        str - String with band's id, name and URL to an example song separated by a tab "\t"
        Returns:
        a new BandInfo from given str or null if for any reason str is not in valid format

      • getBands

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,BandInfo> getBands(java.nio.file.Path filePath)
                                                          throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a Map from a file, where every line contains information about a single band.
        Lines are processed by fromString(String) method.
        Parameters:
        filePath - Path of the file
        Returns:
        Map with band's id number as a key and BandInfo as a value
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs

      • getBandsWithVotes

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,BandInfo> getBandsWithVotes(java.nio.file.Path bandsFile,
                                                                          java.nio.file.Path votesFile)
                                                                   throws java.io.IOException
        Same as getBands(Path) method but uses a second file to get the number of votes for each band.
        Parameters:
        bandsFile - Path of the file with information about bands
        votesFile - Path of the file with number of votes for each band
        Returns:
        Map with band's id number as a key and BandInfo as a value
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs
